# JLA Link — Git Sync Workflow

After completing any code or content changes to this project, **always sync to GitHub** unless the user explicitly says not to.

## Required steps

1. Run `git status` and `git diff` to review changes.
2. Stage relevant files with `git add` (never commit `.env*` or secrets).
3. Commit with a clear, concise message describing the change.
4. Push to `origin main` (`git push`).
5. Confirm sync succeeded (`git status` shows clean and up to date with `origin/main`).

## Commit author

If git identity is not configured, use one-time env vars or `-c user.name=... -c user.email=...` — do not update global git config.

## Remote

- Repository: `https://github.com/jenneilai/jlalink.git`
- Branch: `main`

## When to skip

Only skip commit/push when the user explicitly requests local-only changes or says not to push.
